This paper is about creating a large annotated medical image dataset for the development and evaluation of segmentation algorithms. The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for semantic segmentation of medical images. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for segmentation, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence for medical image segmentation, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of medical imaging, which makes cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of benchmarking and evaluation of segmentation algorithms, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category.
